article.description: Zach Hunsaker had 20 points as Brown got past Cornell 74-63 on Friday night.
article.headline: Hunsaker scores 20 to lead Brown past Cornell 74-63
article.linkText: Hunsaker scores 20 to lead Brown past Cornell 74-63
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Zach Hunsaker had 20 points as Brown got past Cornell 74-63 on Friday night. Tamenang Choh had 14 points for Brown (8-8, 1-2 Ivy League). Jaylan Gainey added 12 points and eight rebounds. Brandon Anderson, who led the Bears in scoring entering the matchup with 19 points per game, had 7 points on 1-of-16 shooting. Josh Warren had 17 points for the Big Red (4-12, 1-2). Jimmy Boeheim added 12 points and eight rebounds. Terrance McBride had 11 points. Brown takes on Columbia at home on Saturday. Cornell plays Yale on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
